          <from>HON. STERLING BELLIVEAU</from>
          <p>HON. STERLING BELLIVEAU : Mr. Speaker, my question also is to the Minister of Fisheries and Aquaculture. Recently, the Minister of Fisheries and Aquaculture announced that a 2 cent per pound levy would be imposed on lobster sales, to be used to help promote the sale of lobsters locally, nationally and internationally. As of March 27th, a government release stated, "Fishermen, buyers, shippers and processors all endorsed a levy to support the marketing of Canadian lobster during the Canadian Lobster Value Recovery Summit."</p>
